---

GitHub upload + GitHub Pages

1) Initialize git at workspace root:

git init
git add .
git commit -m "init: hub backend and github pages frontend"

2) Create GitHub repository (example: camera_lab_server), then bind remote and push:

git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/<your-account>/camera_lab_server.git
git push -u origin main

3) Enable GitHub Pages:

- Repository Settings -> Pages
- Build and deployment -> Source: Deploy from a branch
- Branch: main, Folder: /docs

4) Open page URL after deployment:

https://<your-account>.github.io/camera_lab_server/

5) Set backend API Base on the page:

- The docs page supports custom API Base input (for example https://your-server-host)
- If API Base is empty, it uses same-origin /api/*
